To install amazon_CLI_v2
---------------------------------------
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install

To make system aware that sensitive information are stored in the folders below:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
export AWS_CONFIG_FILE=~/.aws/config                                                                       âœ˜ 252
export AWS_SHARED_CREDENTIALS_FILE=~/.aws/credentials

Launching and executing services in aws has the following general syntax:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
aws [option] <command> <sub-command> [params]

--filter option is useful to limit the stdout stream 
--query work for filtering and works on almost all aws <sub-commands>
